constructor.details: pythPriceFeedAddress will be different for each chain and can be found here: https://docs.pyth.network/documentation/pythnet-price-feeds/evmpairPriceFeedAddressId are the same for EVM chains and can be found here: https://pyth.network/developers/price-feed-ids#pyth-evm-mainnet

params.maxOpenInterest: (precision 1e18) Array for the max amount of interest alowed to open for a pair. this protects the protocol and the user. This can be adjusted as the protocol matures
params.pairPriceFeedAddressId: is the pyth price feed id for asset pair e.g. ETH/USD
params.pairSymbol: this will be an array of the all the trading pairs symbols e.g. ["ETH/USD", "BTC/USD", "XRP/USD"...]
params.pythPriceFeedAddress: is the contract address that will be used to retrieve the price feed data
params.tokenCollateralAddress: is the ERC20 token address that will be used as collateral for trades. Expected precision is 1e18

liquidateUser(address,uint256,uint256,by.details: This can be called by anyone, but most likely a bot to liquidate a user's position

params.pairIndex: index for s_assetPairDetails to retrieve/update the trading pair details
params.priceUpdateData: needed data to update the pyth price feed
params.user: the address of the user that will be liquidated
params.userTradesIdForPair: index for s_userTradeDetails to retrieve/update the user's position details

marketOrder(uint256,int256,int256,uint25.details: bytes[] calldata priceUpdateData is retrieved from the pyth frontend API, check the docs for more details (https://docs.pyth.network/documentation/pythnet-price-feeds/price-service)Always update the pyth price feed manually before getting a price ^^

params.amountCollateral: amount of collateral for the trading position
params.leverage: amount of leverage for the trading position
params.pairIndex: index for s_assetPairDetails to retrieve/update the trading pair details
params.priceUpdateData: needed data to update the pyth price feed

orderClose(uint256,uint256,bytes[]).details: Can only be called by the user with a position open.The function must be called with a value to update the onChain pyth price feed. This fee is retrieved from the pyth api along with the priceUpdateData

params.pairIndex: index for s_assetPairDetails to retrieve/update the trading pair details
params.priceUpdateData: needed data to update the pyth price feed. This is retrieved from pyth's off chain api will be verified on chain.
params.userTradesIdForPair: trade per pair is capped at 3 thus this value must be 0, 1, or 2. First trade starts @ 2 then 1 and 0.

owner().details: Returns the address of the current owner.

renounceOwnership().details: Leaves the contract without owner. It will not be possible to call `onlyOwner` functions. Can only be called by the current owner. NOTE: Renouncing ownership will leave the contract without an owner, thereby disabling any functionality that is only available to the owner.

transferOwnership(address).details: Transfers ownership of the contract to a new account (`newOwner`). Can only be called by the current owner.

constructor.notice: Sets the initial paramters for the contract

liquidateUser(address,uint256,uint256,by.notice: liquidates a user if there PNL is at zero or below

marketOrder(uint256,int256,int256,uint25.notice: Immediately opens a trading position based on the current market price for an trading pair
